00:16:11.290 --> 00:16:13.700
I, I love you.

00:16:13.700 --> 00:16:14.830
What?

00:16:14.830 --> 00:16:19.540
Your hands! I love your hands,
they're--they're nice!

00:16:19.540 --> 00:16:20.370
My hands?

00:16:20.370 --> 00:16:23.200
Yeah! I was just thinking, "Man, I love 'em!"

00:16:23.200 --> 00:16:28.000
Thanks. And I hold my pencil right,
so I don't have a callus like you.

00:16:28.000 --> 00:16:31.160
H-Hey! No fair!

00:16:31.160 --> 00:16:34.290
Well, cool.

00:16:34.290 --> 00:16:37.750
I love yours, too.

00:16:37.750 --> 00:16:39.290
Okay.

00:16:41.000 --> 00:16:42.700
I love you.

00:16:43.830 --> 00:16:46.330
Yeah, I heard you.

00:16:46.330 --> 00:16:47.750
Okay.

00:16:48.870 --> 00:16:50.500
I'm back!

00:16:50.500 --> 00:16:51.750
Hey, there!

00:16:51.750 --> 00:16:53.620
Sota! Did you wash your hands?

00:16:53.620 --> 00:16:55.200
Not yet!

00:16:55.200 --> 00:16:57.000
What're you doing?

00:16:57.000 --> 00:17:02.080
Hori-san put the DVDs back in
the wrong cases, so I'm fixing it.

00:17:05.540 --> 00:17:09.200
C'mon, time for dinner!

00:17:09.200 --> 00:17:12.540
Wash your hands, first!
You're eating with us, right, Miyamura?

00:17:12.540 --> 00:17:14.830
Oh, yeah, if that's okay.

00:17:14.830 --> 00:17:17.410
Okay, then you and Sota
need to go wash your hands!

00:17:17.410 --> 00:17:20.500
You got it. Let's go, Sota.

00:17:20.500 --> 00:17:21.950
Okay!

00:17:33.830 --> 00:17:35.750
So I was just talking to her,

00:17:35.750 --> 00:17:38.250
and she said she's "never
letting me have Miyamura-kun"!

00:17:38.250 --> 00:17:39.370
What?

00:17:39.370 --> 00:17:43.410
I mean, I was just joking,
but she got like, actually mad!

00:17:43.410 --> 00:17:46.410
That's 'cause you take
your jokes <i>way </i>too far, Remi.

00:17:46.410 --> 00:17:48.910
Yeah, but still!

00:17:48.910 --> 00:17:52.200
Hori-san was sooo scary.

00:17:59.910 --> 00:18:03.120
Morning, Miyamura!

00:18:03.120 --> 00:18:05.040
Morning.

00:18:05.040 --> 00:18:08.080
What?! What happened to your face?!

00:18:08.080 --> 00:18:12.000
I got into a fight and got hit in the face.

00:18:12.000 --> 00:18:15.000
You got into a fight? With who?

00:18:15.000 --> 00:18:16.120
Ishikawa-kun.

00:18:16.120 --> 00:18:17.250
With Toru?!

00:18:17.250 --> 00:18:18.910
I mean, sure, he's a big dummy dum-dum,

00:18:18.910 --> 00:18:21.500
but I never thought he'd
get violent with a friend.

00:18:21.500 --> 00:18:24.160
U-Uhh, Hori-san, actually--

00:18:24.160 --> 00:18:26.750
Nope, I don't want to hear it.

00:18:26.750 --> 00:18:30.290
I know <i>just </i>the kind
of guy he is now, thank you!

00:18:30.290 --> 00:18:31.750
Morning, Ishikawa!

00:18:31.750 --> 00:18:33.160
Whoa, holy shit!

00:18:33.160 --> 00:18:34.750
Toru!

00:18:34.750 --> 00:18:37.250
Hey, mornin'.

00:18:42.120 --> 00:18:44.330
You got into a fight?

00:18:44.330 --> 00:18:45.540
Yeah.

00:18:45.540 --> 00:18:47.540
So you beat the crap out of each other?

00:18:47.540 --> 00:18:50.330
No, not really...

00:18:50.330 --> 00:18:53.370
I dodged everything 'cept that first punch.

00:18:53.370 --> 00:18:55.700 line:20%
"ashamed"

00:18:53.370 --> 00:18:55.700
Then I beat Ishikawa-kun to a pulp...

00:18:55.700 --> 00:18:56.040
Then I beat Ishikawa-kun to a pulp...

00:18:56.040 --> 00:18:59.040
You're kinda scary, Miyamura.

00:18:59.040 --> 00:19:00.750
Why were you fighting?

00:19:02.410 --> 00:19:04.330
It's none of your business, Hori.

00:19:04.330 --> 00:19:09.620
Okay, fine. I still can't believe
you two got into an actual fight.

00:19:11.540 --> 00:19:14.950
So, Toru, who won? You or him?

00:19:16.120 --> 00:19:18.200
What's that look for?

00:19:18.200 --> 00:19:20.660
Oh, nothing.

00:19:20.660 --> 00:19:23.830
Pretty sure I lost.

00:19:26.750 --> 00:19:29.540
Look, I know it's not happening, okay?

00:19:29.540 --> 00:19:30.450
Okay.

00:19:30.450 --> 00:19:33.080
Seriously, dude, <i>listen</i>!

00:19:33.080 --> 00:19:35.750
I'm listening! I swear!

00:19:35.750 --> 00:19:38.500
Hori's in love with you, Miyamura.

00:19:38.500 --> 00:19:42.200
You mentioned that before,
but I still think you're wrong.

00:19:42.200 --> 00:19:43.830
You're just imagining things--

00:19:43.830 --> 00:19:45.370
I am not!

00:19:46.450 --> 00:19:49.700
How would you react if I said I wasn't?

00:19:49.700 --> 00:19:51.120
Are you trying to psych me out?

00:19:51.120 --> 00:19:56.450
If Hori said, to your face,
that she loves you, what would you say?

00:19:56.450 --> 00:19:58.660
Would you just brush it off like that?

00:19:59.870 --> 00:20:03.080
Hori-san just sees me as a friend.

00:20:03.080 --> 00:20:05.750
Why do you keep going back to that?

00:20:05.750 --> 00:20:09.120
Because if I don't, you'll keep
asking me the same question.

00:20:09.120 --> 00:20:10.500
Well, yeah, but...

00:20:10.500 --> 00:20:12.450
Besides, it's obvious
she doesn't like me like that.

00:20:12.450 --> 00:20:15.950
I'd like to know why you think you're right.

00:20:15.950 --> 00:20:17.700
Well--!

00:20:17.700 --> 00:20:22.410
I know your own feelings
probably influence your perception,

00:20:22.410 --> 00:20:25.540
but you can't assume how
Hori-san feels without asking her.

00:20:25.540 --> 00:20:26.160
Look!

